org.eclipse.incquery.xcore.util

Class IncQueryXcoreEcoreBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.emf.ecore.xcore.util.XcoreEcoreBuilder
      • org.eclipse.incquery.xcore.util.IncQueryXcoreEcoreBuilder

  • public class IncQueryXcoreEcoreBuilder
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.xcore.util.XcoreEcoreBuilder
    The Ecore builder is responsible to create the Ecore model for the IncQuery & Xcore specific metamodel. Apart from mapping all Xcore related model elements to Ecore specific model elements, it also needs to register the setting delegates related annotations on both the EPackage and the EStructuralFeatures. This class will be used in the dynamic instance model use case.

    The specified runtime annotations will then be used in the runtime Eclipse for the loaded Dynamic Instance Model.
    (1) The EPackage will have an annotation with the source EcorePackage.eNS_URI, key "settingDelegates" and value "org.eclipse.incquery.querybasedfeature".
    (2) The EStructuralFeatures will have an annotation with the source "org.eclipse.incquery.querybasedfeature", key "patternFQN" and the value will be the fully qualified name of the EIQ pattern which provides the value of the feature. The EStructuralFeature.Internal.SettingDelegates will be loaded with the use of the special editor, specifically tailored for this scenario.
    Author:
    Tamas Szabo (itemis AG)
